                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, my question deals with how to get a pissed off mob to forget about me.  The scenario I'm in is me tri-boxing in OoW "Watering Hole" Expedition, 67 Enchanter / 67 Mage / 67 Druid.
<br />

<br />
How I have been doing things:
<br />

<br />
Enchanter Pacifies if the mobs would pull two, Mage pulls with a debuff (so I don't get tash agro), send pet.  Enchanter slows and cripples gets close to get smacked once so pet attacks (with rune I don't take damage). Toss a heal or two and the fights over.  Everythings great.
<br />

<br />
BUT..  sometimes I DO get two mobs.  I lock one mob down with bliss, and do everything the same and the one mob dies.  In the meantime though, I have slowed and crippled the add, and Gnome is it PISSED.
<br />

<br />
I have tried memblur, Recurring amnesia, but it keeps coming after me.  last time I just went invis and ran back to zone in and let mage COH me back.
<br />

<br />
Would lots of Boggles work in this case ?  How do I clear the hatelist without CoH?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
