                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Don't forget pacification.  If the mob is in camp, it is usually close enough to reaggro.  Wiping its memory isn't enough; you have to keep it from noticing you again.
<br />

<br />
My tactic:
<br />
Mez
<br />
Wait about 15 seconds
<br />
Pacify (pacification has shorter duration than mez and still needs to be in effect until after mez wears off)
<br />
Memblur
<br />
Recurring anmesia
<br />
Memblur
<br />
Memblur
<br />

<br />
I don't have the memblur AA.  Thats why I use two memblur spells and repeat the memblur.  Work on the assumption that only one in four works.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=554032" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sunaeri LaSuin</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.artofbuilding.net" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Art of Building</a> (a mud builders' resource)</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Sunaeri on Thu Oct 28, 2004 3:29 pm; edited 4 times in total</span></td>
