<br />
Err......
<br />
You boggle a mezzed mob?
<br />
Bad idea in my experience.
<br />
If you want to remain indefinitely on the mobs hate list... boggle it when it's mezzed. For some odd reason boggle seems to have the opposite effect on a mezzed mob (least that's what I found) than memblur.
<br />
I mez, tash (or vice versa), slow, memblur. Remez if needed, memblur. If it heads at me after mez is broken, I boggle.
<br />

<br />
I don't know if anyone else had the 'cannot get off hate list after boggling mezzed mob' phenomena... but... I had it happen enough to quit doing it.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
