                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Disclaimer: I only have EF rank 2 so far but the next 36 AA points are going for the remaining ranks. I use the level 55 spell  Mem Flux.
<br />

<br />
It doesn't work all the time but when it does its spectacular.
<br />

<br />
Example: Our Rathe Council CC group was 4 enc's and 2 bard's. When the time came to kill them all, everyone in the group except me died on mezz break.
<br />

<br />
Example: To amuse myself, when multi pulls are incoming to the raid, I target an add and blur it, nice to see a mob just turn around and start walking home while the pullers go wtf!
<br />

<br />
I now have a mem blur spell permanently loaded and will always blur a mob that I mezz. This is by far the most useful defensive spell we have, I highly recommend it.
<br />

<br />
Sleight
<br />

<br />
ps The Rathe event was the last my guild needed for time access.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
