                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">BoF does 2 20% checks -- Mem Flux does one 30% check.
<br />

<br />
If EF adds to mem blur chance, and BoF is 10% worse chance (but tries twice), then you need &gt; .99% success rate on Mem Flux or &lt; 21% chance for Flux to be more reliable than BoF.
<br />

<br />
(If flux has a 98% chance of succeeding, BoF does two 88% chances.  The chance BoF fails twice is 12% * 12% or 1.4%, which means it has a 98.6% chance of succeeding.)
<br />

<br />
In other words, it might be the case that BoF is more reliable than mem flux until mem flux is 100% reliable.  BoF has the problem that it can hit extra mobs you don't want to blur.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
