                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The way I handle this in my groups is to keep two mezzes up that will work on the mobs I'm fighting.  In the Fire Pit, for example, I use Apathy and Sleep, which work on all but the named.  When I mez with Apathy then debuff, I refresh the mez with Sleep since it will cancel the old mez and therefore get a chance to memblur.  Recasting the same mez adds aggro without any other benefit than refreshing the mez timer.
<br />

<br />
I always swap mezzes back and forth for the blur, since the higher level ones are usually only 25 more mana (Bliss and Sleep, for example).  I very rarely have aggro when the tank grabs the mezzed mob, it's as reliable as memory flux, and cheaper.  Plus, it gives you another 54 seconds of mez.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
